------------- CUSTOMIZATION -------------
Once your Kobold has been made Dynamic, you are able to change its colors. Currently, you have a few options for doing this;
1.) The Dynamicizer can be used can change your head, skin, hair and tattoo colors. However, the full palette of colors is not currently available with this method.
2.) You can politely ask a DM while in game to change your skin color, if you have the reference number for the desired color handy.
3.) The Hair and Tattoo NPCs at Kampo's and various other locations in game can alter your kobold's colors at any time for a fee.

Follow the NPC instructions and use this reference to find the number of your desired color:

  Hair color = Eye color
  Skin color = Scale color
  Tattoo 1 color = Ear holes, eye ridge
  Tattoo 2 color = Teeth, horns, talons


To change your kobold's base clothing colors once it has been made Dynamic, set all armor appearances to 0 (which is actually appearance #2, in most cases) and set your desired colors:

  Cloth 2 = Clothing color
  Metal 2 = Bracelet color


To change your kobold's head once it has been made Dynamic, use the Dynamicizer. You have the 3 choices of head type in addition to the default. This becomes your default head, which will be covered by an equipped helmet.


Pelvis 2 is the only Pelvis option that will show the Kobold's tail.

Most Robe options hide the tail. The following Robe options have a visible tail:

  Robe 6 (Long coat with cloth shirt)*
  Robe 7 (Long coat with chain shirt)*
  * Tail clips through the long coat
  Robe 26 (Hat with feather)
  Robe 35 (Fancy coat)
  Robe 45 (Circlet)


Additionally, Kobolds have the option to ask for a free tail swap to a lizard tail in chromatic or metallic dragon colors. To see all of the options available, use the Search function on the forum with "The Compiled Kobold Information Thread" as the query.

------------- TROUBLESHOOTING -------------
If the Dyanicizer won't let change your Kobold to the Dynamic Model, contact a DM for assistance. This is either because your Kobold is female (see below) and/or because you need your Kobold Phenotype to be changed to "A". Don't worry, the DMs will know what this means, and both of these can be easily requested. After this is done, you can use the Dynamicizer!

Female kobolds cannot be changed to the Dynamic model. You can have a female kobold that is mechanically male by requesting it from a DM while in game or by posting your request in the Leto & Maintenance subforum of the Requests forum. If you can provide your character's file name in the Leto request, it should help the DMs process your request. You can pull up the file name by typing or copying in the following line while in game:
                  /s f_file show vault

After the gender is changed, they will keep their original voice set. If you would like to have their voice set changed to one of the Kobold monster voicesets, you can include that in your Leto request.

Amia supports the following subraces:

DWARF : Shield Dwarf (default), Gold Dwarf, Duergar

ELF : Moon Elf (default), Drow, Sun Elf, Wild Elf, Wood Elf, Feytouched

GNOME : Rock Gnome (default), Svirfneblin

HALF-ELF : Half-Elf (fefault), Half-Drow

HALFLING : Lightfoot Halfling (default), Ghostwise Halfling, Strongheart Halfling, Goblin, Kobold

HALF-ORC : Half-Orc (default), Hobgoblin, Ogrillion, Orog

HUMAN : Non-regional (default), Calishite, Chultan, Damaran, Durpari, Ffolk, Halruaan, Mulan, Shadovar, Tuigan

ANY : Aasimar, Air Genasi, Earth Genasi, Fire Genasi, Water Genasi, Tiefling

The following subraces are also available with a DM approved request:

Aquatic Elf, Fey'ri, Shadow Elf, Snow Elf, Elfling

For information on these subraces, go to http://www.amiaworld.net/phpbb3/index.php and click on the "Subraces" section on the left sidebar.

To play a subrace, simply pick the correct Race and then type in its recognised word (case insensitive) in the subrace field of the Character Creation Menu. The stats presented in the table below override the standard racial modifiers (for example, you will not receive both Dwarf and Duergar bonuses). The system first removes your NWN base race bonuses, then adds Amia subrace bonuses. In other words, the character will be reduced to a human stat-wise. All bonuses you saw in creation screen are nulled, and the final bonuses are the ones you can read from the table below.

Use the Subrace Activator to apply your racial abilities. Some subraces require a special request before they can be played on Amia, and any race not included in the subrace options (and some which are) also require a request to play. If you wish to play a special race, you can apply to do so on the forums, but do not make the special character until the request has been approved.

Playing a character with non-standard skin tones for the race or a non-supported class requires a request (a white-skinned Chultan, black-skinned elf, pale-skinned drow and so on...).

Read more about character applications in the stickies of the Requests forum!

* Leave the subrace field blank, if you do not wish a subrace from Amia's selection! Adding an unrecognised word to the subrace field will prevent you from entering the game world.
* Do NOT add any other words to Subrace field in character creation screen, than those listed here! As above, adding an unrecognized word will prevent you from entering.
* Outsiders by their nature are extremely susceptible to certain magical spells, such as Banishment and Word of Faith.
* Light sensitivity: If you’re exposed to bright light then your eyes become overstimulated and you’ll suffer the following penalties: -1 to attack rolls, Search checks, and Spot checks.
* Level Adjustment: A number that’s added to your character’s total Hit Dice to determine the Effective Character Level (ECL), which represents the overall power of your character. This also affects the highest level you can reach as a character. An ECL +2 character can only reach level 28, and can ECL +1 character can only reach level 29.

The Waiting Rooms are for those performing any kind of OOC maintenance that is not fulfilled by the self-service utilities in the Domaintenance or Species Assignment areas.

If you...
... need help with a rebuild/request
... need a port back to a DM event
... are arranging your inventory
... are reviewing your character sheet
... are coordinating details before going IG
... need any other DM assistance
... are in the OOC areas for any reason

Please use these rooms instead of remaining in the main entry, so as to reduce load time and the potential of crashing for other players who are logging in.
